# Solana Patterns

## Code Location

All blockchain-specific code lives in `server/solana/` and `lib/solana/`. Keep Solana logic out of React components — components call services via tRPC, services call Solana modules.

## Key Modules

- `lib/solana/connection.ts` — Shared Solana RPC connection
- `lib/solana/rpc-limiter.ts` — Rate limiting for RPC calls
- `server/solana/jito-bundle.ts` — Jito bundle submission and confirmation
- `server/solana/jito-client.ts` — Jito block engine client
- `server/solana/bundle-create-and-buy.ts` — Bundle creation for token launch
- `server/solana/bundle-transaction-builder.ts` — Transaction construction for bundles
- `server/solana/launch-dev-buy.ts` — Dev wallet buy transaction
- `server/solana/pump-transaction-builders.ts` — Pump.fun buy/sell transaction builders
- `server/solana/pump-quotes.ts` — Bonding curve price quotes
- `server/solana/pump-idl.ts` / `pump-new-idl.ts` — Pump.fun program IDL
- `server/solana/grpc-manager.ts` — Yellowstone gRPC connection management
- `server/solana/grpc-utils.ts` — gRPC helper utilities
- `server/solana/shyft-grpc.ts` — Shyft gRPC integration
- `server/solana/token-transactions-grpc.ts` — Transaction monitoring via gRPC
- `server/solana/volume-bot-grpc.ts` — Volume bot gRPC monitoring

## Conventions

- Handle RPC errors and implement retries — Solana RPC is unreliable
- Use `rpc-limiter` to avoid hitting rate limits
- Validate transaction signatures before processing results
- Use Jito bundles for atomic multi-transaction operations (launch, exit)
- Bundle tips are configured via `lib/config/jito.config.ts`
- gRPC (Yellowstone) is used for real-time transaction monitoring; access is gated by user plan
- Shyft provides complementary data: REST APIs, DeFi pool info, webhook-based ingestion

## Transaction Building

- Build transactions in `server/solana/`, not in services
- Services orchestrate the flow: prepare data → call transaction builder → submit → handle result
- Keep transaction construction pure (deterministic given inputs)
- Test transaction builders independently (see `*.test.ts` files in `server/solana/`)

## Error Handling

- Solana transaction errors should be caught and mapped to `AppError` with user-friendly messages
- Log RPC errors with context (endpoint, method, duration) but never log private keys
- Handle common failure modes: insufficient funds, slippage exceeded, transaction expired, RPC timeout
